decision

Class DecisionResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • decision.DecisionResult

  • public class DecisionResult
extends java.lang.Object
    Decision object with unique information for each farm. This object can output a gams compatible simulation file, as well as output a log of all decisions and parameters during the model execution. This object contains a public 2d array of the pre/post sowing strategies that correspond to the 72 strategies in the model.
    Author:
    kellerke

    • Field Detail

      • activitySets

        public static int[][] activitySets
        We have 72 activities in the system, and these tuples correspond to each activity. first element in the tuple is a row in the activity matrix, and the second element is the column. Each row element corresponds to a post sowing strategy, and each column is a pre sowing strategy. So [53,2] corresponds to post_strat 53, and pre_strat 2 strategy set.

      • activity_matrix

        public static int[][] activity_matrix
        empty matrix for the output gams file. The matrix corresponds to a 55 row by 6 column matrix where each row is a post strategy and the columns are a pre strategy

    • Method Detail

      • appendMPInput

        public void appendMPInput()
        Create the files that contain the parameters required to run the gams simulation.
        Use the strategy matrix variable that is 55x6 elements and set a specific bit pattern based on the selected strategy. Each strategy corresponds to a StrategySet tuple value which sets the correct 1 in the matrix.

      • appendLogFile

        public void appendLogFile(java.lang.String fileName)
        write output CSV log file based on decision object. This log file can be updated each time period for each agent.
        Parameters:
        fileName - of output file which is previously checked to ensure we will not exceed 1 million lines of data.
